  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN150.1-kilavi">pakaṟkuṟi vantu kaṇṇuṟṟu nīṅkun talaimakaṉait tōḻi <app><lem>talaimakaḷai yiṭattuyttu</lem><rdg wit="#C5 #C7 #G1 #G2">talaimakaḷ yiṭattuyttu vantu</rdg><rdg wit="#C3">talaimakaṉai yetirppaṭṭu niṉṟu</rdg></app> ceṟippaṟivuṟīi varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How the confidante informed HIM, who had come to the day tryst, met [HER and] left, of [HER] confinement [and] urged for marriage after having sent HER to the place.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN150.1">
              <l>piṉṉu<supplied>vi</supplied>ṭa neṟitta kūntalum poṉṉē</l>
              <l>vāka<supplied>t taru</supplied>mpiya taṇaṅkum vampuviṭa</l>
              <l>kaṇṇurut teḻutaru mulaiyu nōkki</l>
              <l>yelliṉai periteṉap paṉmāṇ kūṟip</l>
              <l>peruntō ḷaṭaiya muyaṅki nīṭuniṉain</l>
              <l>taruṅkaṭip paṭuttaṉaḷ <supplied>yāyē</supplied> kaṭuñcellā</l>
              <l>vāṭcuṟā vaḻaṅkum vaḷaimēy peruntuṟaik</l>
              <l>ka<supplied>ṉai</supplied>tta neytaṟ kaṇpōṉ māmalar</l>
              <l>naṉaitta <supplied>ceru</supplied>ntip pōtuvā ya<supplied>viḻa</supplied></l>
              <l>mālai maṇiyitaḻ kūmpak kālaik</l>
              <l>kaṇṇāṟu kāviyoṭu taṇṇeṉa malaruṅ</l>
              <l>ka<supplied>ḻi</supplied>yuṅ kāṉaluṅ kāṇṭoṟum palapulantu</l>
              <l>vaḷarā colleṉap paruvan<del>tan</del></l>
              <l>tārār mārpanī taṇanta ñāṉṟē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Looking at [her] curled tresses, when the braids came loose,</l>
                <l>at the torment that has budded on [her] bosom − golden –,</l>
                <l>and at [her] breasts that rise, the nipples taking shape, when [her] bodice came loose (1-3)</l>
                <l>saying many times “your [are] very splendid”, (4)</l>
                <l>closely embracing [her] wide shoulders, thinking long, (5)</l>
                <l>mother did ordain heavy protection, (6a-c)</l>
                <l>− at the time you departed, you with a chest full of garlands, (14)</l>
                <l>at a season to say “words will not prosper”, (13)</l>
                <l>being vexed much each time you saw the seashore grove and the backwaters, (12)</l>
                <l>where the eye-like huge flowers of the blue waterlily that matured (8)</l>
                <l>by the big ghat foraged by mussels, where swordfish roam without going fast, (6d-7)</l>
                <l>bloom coolly along with the blue lotus, fragrant with nectar, (11)</l>
                <l>in the morning when [its] sapphire petals close, in the evening (10)</l>
                <l>when the bud mouths open on the budding pear-tree. (9)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
